  "prompt": "How do you say \"thank you\" in your language?",
  "response": "I don't have a native language, but I can provide translations for \"thank you\" in several languages:\n\n- **Spanish:** Gracias\n- **French:** Merci\n- **German:** Danke\n- **Italian:** Grazie\n- **Portuguese:** Obrigado (if you're male) / Obrigada (if you're female)\n- **Japanese:** \u3042\u308a\u304c\u3068\u3046 (Arigat\u014d)\n- **Chinese (Mandarin):** \u8c22\u8c22 (Xi\u00e8xi\u00e8)\n- **Korean:** \uac10\uc0ac\ud569\ub2c8\ub2e4 (Gamsahamnida)\n- **Russian:** \u0421\u043f\u0430\u0441\u0438\u0431\u043e (Spasibo)\n- **Arabic:** \u0634\u0643\u0631\u0627 (Shukran)\n- **Hindi:** \u0927\u0928\u094d\u092f\u0935\u093e\u0926 (Dhanyavaad)\n- **Swahili:** Asante\n- **Turkish:** Te\u015fekk\u00fcr ederim\n- **Greek:** \u0395\u03c5\u03c7\u03b1\u03c1\u03b9\u03c3\u03c4\u03ce (Efharist\u00f3)\n- **Dutch:** Dank je wel / Dank u wel\n\nIf you need the translation for a specific language not listed here, feel free to ask!",
